headline: ENPH Q1 Earnings Call: Tariffs and Product Launches Shape Outlook Amid Market Headwinds
summary: Home energy technology company Enphase (NASDAQ:ENPH) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 35.2% year on year to $356.1 million. On the other hand, the company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $360 million, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.68 per share was 6% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
